749:  Under Čech-acyclicity and $\HasCechToHModuleIso$, if $\bigsqcup \mathfrak U_i = U$, then $H^{\prime n}(U, \mathcal F)$ is a subsingleton for $n \ge 1$.
767:\subsection{Affine Čech-acyclic cover carrier}
769:The predicate $\IsAffineHModuleVanishing$ (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_IsAffineHModuleVanishing}) requires vanishing on every affine open. To instantiate it from Čech data, we introduce a carrier class that bundles the existence of a suitable cover per affine open.
771:\begin{definition}[Affine Čech-acyclic cover carrier]
775:  For every affine open $U$, there exists an indexed cover $\mathfrak U$ with $\bigsqcup \mathfrak U_i = U$ that is Čech-acyclic and carries a comparison isomorphism.
794:  \label{def:Scheme_basicOpenCover}
795:  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.basicOpenCover}
